<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-599-602  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 599 602.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Sept 4 1989 n433 p17(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sysorex ties growth to federal market. (Sysorex InformationSystems Inc.) (company profile)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gerber, Cheryl.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sysorex Information Systems Inc, a privately-held US governmentsystems integrator, has been awakened from its dormancy with theaward of three federal systems integration contracts.andP;  These are a$77.4 million US Postal Service contract, a $16.2 million NationalAgricultural Statistics Service contract, and a $24.9 millionDepartment of Justice, Immigration and Naturalization Servicecontract.andP;  Sysorex's business upswing follows the hiring of fourElectronic Data Systems Corp executives in April 1988.andP;  The teamadapted a tactical rather than a strategic approach to systemsintegration by concentrating on action rather than planning.andO;Sysorex answered 15 requests for proposals in 15 months.andP;  The newcontracts, along with current business, could earn Sysorex about$50 million for the fiscal year ending Sep 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sysorex Information Systems Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Company ProfileComputer Systems IntegratorsUnited States. Postal ServiceGovernment ContractsManagementUnited States. National Agricultural Statistics ServiceUnited States. Immigration and Naturalization ServiceGrowth.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>